"n.水坑，洼 【英】 n.水坑，洼(a very small pool of dirty or muddy water) 【记】 注意不要和peddle(沿 街叫卖)相混 n. 水坑(一小池雨水) 【区】peddle(v 沿街叫卖); pebble(n 卵石) 【记】pool + 音：抖，在pool里抖；pool 斗，pool形成的一个斗→水坑；音：扑腾，在水洼里扑腾 puddle (n.)  early 14c., ""small pool of dirty water,"" frequentative or diminutive of Old English pudd ""ditch,"" related to German pudeln ""to splash in water"" (compare poodle). Originally used of pools and ponds as well. puddle (v.)  ""to dabble in water, poke in mud,"" mid-15c., from puddle (n.); extended sense in iron manufacture is ""turn and stir (molten iron) in a furnace."" Related: Puddled; puddling."
